<paragraph id="48EC84BEDB0E0275972EC14329F14978" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
Basidiospores [60/3/3] (6.8) 7.9-8.8-9.9 (10.7) 
<normalizedToken id="C375969D672094FD3640BD43547E3ACD" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(3.7) 4.6-5.2-5.8 (6.3) 
<normalizedToken id="085D50B3251FF4DF2991DB821073F7B2" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
[
<emphasis id="71DB1BA58028F9DD49A7400E8A5CB24D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Q</emphasis>
= 1.59-1.88, 
<emphasis id="B60E9E8BD28275EAD1095647D5D0E5D5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Q</emphasis>
= 1.70 
<normalizedToken id="47EB8B8AF2A27E15595300CE662738ED" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.065], narrowly ellipsoid or cylindrical, hyaline, guttulate, thin-walled, inamyloid. Basidia 32-46 
<normalizedToken id="EEE54BD52D15A7B2EFEA46FC1AD045CF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-9 
<normalizedToken id="9C66CB483453EEEE791979C7B75889EB" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, hyaline, clavate, 4-spored. Cheilocystidia 27-49 
<normalizedToken id="FC2F6D30D697A1D3737A58238C989A98" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-9 
<normalizedToken id="E6DB81BD25E73D8F6BC417F268EA5D85" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, abundant, irregularly cylindric or clavate, colorless. Pleurocystidia absent. Lamellar trama subregular; hyphae 3-9 
<normalizedToken id="FDDF3C334B4CCC9604F786CF55892411" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide, thin-walled, hyaline, inamyloid. Pileus trama subregular, sarcodimitic. Pileipellis hyphae 2-5 
<normalizedToken id="0597F722725959DBE0C10DC75C4C8C72" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide, light yellow (2B2), a cutis; terminal elements cylindric or clavate, 31-50 
<normalizedToken id="93BE414EF5B81FC0B3A0F13B08A75ECF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-9 
<normalizedToken id="451A35058BCA92A6F0A6614A111769D6" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, light yellowish brown (2C4) to yellowish brown (2C6) pigmented, especially in the apex; true pileocystidia absent. Hyphae of the stipitipellis 3-6 
<normalizedToken id="91374AEA5092C81D60E352745856978B" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide, hyaline, smooth; caulocystidia cylindrical or broadly clavate, 32-48 
<normalizedToken id="7F753083307C051FAAD0A1593FF9103C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-8 
<normalizedToken id="F4D42A1B65AE6EF44645B7C3186046D9" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, hyaline, thin-walled. All tissues nonreactive in iodine. Clamps present in all tissues.
</paragraph>
<caption id="4ED59AC08D65BC4DCBEF8BA0E203380D" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.89.79864.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/678687" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" start="Figure 12" startId="F12">
