<subSubSection id="CCE32C0639FEA89FC490C0A30D626A43" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="8C77C05BA1DCFBB7E84E25AB10F1E5E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F3A257F05BA692F06F622488C17EE65" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
Having a sarcodimitic tissue structure, 
<taxonomicName id="4B0C54446E4F9A967F52A6796390A3F6" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. nemorale" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis id="F7DC41696B5C5AE467B8BEEC637E55F9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits well within the currently restricted concept of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="23F7D504895B5A8A08A11F102DAEBAF2" authorityName="Singer" authorityYear="1951" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="20E3B7ACF85DBC7BD3847398084ABC54" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BC3040656FF10E9843B8ED8423449E81" author="Redhead, SA" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" refId="B50" refString="Redhead, SA, 1986. Mycological observations: 17-20, nomenclatural notes on some omphaloid genera in Canada: Chrysomphalina, Rickenella, Gerronema, Omphalina. Acta Mycologica Sinica Suppl: 297-304." title="Mycological observations: 17 - 20, nomenclatural notes on some omphaloid genera in Canada: Chrysomphalina, Rickenella, Gerronema, Omphalina. Acta Mycologica Sinica Suppl: 297 - 304." year="1986">Redhead 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="213DDBCE72C3D72D955A7D483AC27405" author="Norvell, L" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="379 - 407" refId="B44" refString="Norvell, L, Redhead, S, Ammirati, J, 1994. Omphalina sensu lato in North America 1-2. 1: Omphalina wynniae and the genus Chrysomphalina. 2: Omphalina sensu Bigelow. Mycotaxon 50: 379 - 407" title="Omphalina sensu lato in North America 1 - 2. 1: Omphalina wynniae and the genus Chrysomphalina. 2: Omphalina sensu Bigelow." volume="50" year="1994">Norvell et al. 1994</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="D6948298EE1CD132DACD6C3D37E9CD57" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema nemorale" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis id="268986D095883315DA897C40F3CDBC1C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be rather common in the East Asian region (
<bibRefCitation id="E1B8E2FF815CF404B9E04AA33A34DED6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" author="Takahashi, H" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="15 - 23" refId="B60" refString="Takahashi, H, 2000. Two new species and one new variety of Agaricales from central Honshu, Japan. Mycoscience 41 (1): 15 - 23, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" title="Two new species and one new variety of Agaricales from central Honshu, Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" volume="41" year="2000">Takahashi 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5F8083F5302D534A8474ADEBF6B488D8" DOI="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Czech Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="197 - 212" refId="B1" refString="Antonin, V, Ryoo, R, Shin, HD, 2008. Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea. Czech Mycology 60 (2): 197 - 212, DOI: https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" title="Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" volume="60" year="2008">
<normalizedToken id="2F6654EE40D88607A33C3FE7DCF68B3B" originalValue="Antonín">Antonin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C17A983AF6622482CD7ED78BDABC67AF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" author="Kim, CS" journalOrPublisher="Mycobiology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="22 - 26" refId="B24" refString="Kim, CS, Jo, JW, Kwag, YN, Han, JG, Shrestha, B, Sung, GH, Han, SK, 2014. Taxonomic Re-evaluation of Megacollybia Species in Korea. Mycobiology 42 (1): 22 - 26, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" title="Taxonomic Re-evaluation of Megacollybia Species in Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" volume="42" year="2014">Kim et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="C0416F3D76F7FA9558701D3EE039A5B7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5248/136.249" author="Aqdus, F" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="249 - 259" refId="B4" refString="Aqdus, F, Khalid, AN, 2021. Gerronema nemorale: First report of the genus and species from Pakistan. Mycotaxon 136 (1): 249 - 259, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5248/136.249" title="Gerronema nemorale: First report of the genus and species from Pakistan." url="https://doi.org/10.5248/136.249" volume="136" year="2021">Aqdus and Khalid 2021</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="5BB9F0023700C0B86E98787D4EFA9EF5" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" author="Kim, CS" journalOrPublisher="Mycobiology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="22 - 26" refId="B24" refString="Kim, CS, Jo, JW, Kwag, YN, Han, JG, Shrestha, B, Sung, GH, Han, SK, 2014. Taxonomic Re-evaluation of Megacollybia Species in Korea. Mycobiology 42 (1): 22 - 26, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" title="Taxonomic Re-evaluation of Megacollybia Species in Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" volume="42" year="2014">Kim et al. (2014)</bibRefCitation>
has reported a basidiospore size of 6.0-8.2 
<normalizedToken id="00CFB107FBC18A1D8A9155F089125BE5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-4.8 
<normalizedToken id="36C9E21A8BB209C7EF368E4F68A356D6" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
for 
<taxonomicName id="71B554F7F782D3D0854E8A08D56F480C" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. nemorale" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis id="3E5B5A4B9B247E0419E81D2F25D96BD8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from Mount Halla (Jeju Island) in southwestern Korea, which is distinctly smaller than that of other specimens from Korea, Japan, Pakistan, and our collections (
<bibRefCitation id="AC426FAEDAE7218D2BC109FDE3692B53" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" author="Takahashi, H" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="15 - 23" refId="B60" refString="Takahashi, H, 2000. Two new species and one new variety of Agaricales from central Honshu, Japan. Mycoscience 41 (1): 15 - 23, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" title="Two new species and one new variety of Agaricales from central Honshu, Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/BF02464381" volume="41" year="2000">Takahashi 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="F163E45D83CE87F217BF76440F2B3D8B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" author="Antonin, V" journalOrPublisher="Czech Mycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="197 - 212" refId="B1" refString="Antonin, V, Ryoo, R, Shin, HD, 2008. Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea. Czech Mycology 60 (2): 197 - 212, DOI: https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" title="Gerronema nemorale (Basidiomycota, Agaricomycetes): Anatomic-morphological, cultivational, enzymatic and molecular characteristics and its first records in the Republic of Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.33585/cmy.60204" volume="60" year="2008">
<normalizedToken id="8D23E9C041C3A75663F3F457BDCA9841" originalValue="Antonín">Antonin</normalizedToken>
et al. 2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="95E348105E10A4218F3A032166EDC001" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" author="Kim, CS" journalOrPublisher="Mycobiology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="22 - 26" refId="B24" refString="Kim, CS, Jo, JW, Kwag, YN, Han, JG, Shrestha, B, Sung, GH, Han, SK, 2014. Taxonomic Re-evaluation of Megacollybia Species in Korea. Mycobiology 42 (1): 22 - 26, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" title="Taxonomic Re-evaluation of Megacollybia Species in Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.5941/MYCO.2014.42.1.22" volume="42" year="2014">Kim et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="4B847C76FE8475D450552884ADF5FBE2" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5248/136.249" author="Aqdus, F" journalOrPublisher="Mycotaxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="249 - 259" refId="B4" refString="Aqdus, F, Khalid, AN, 2021. Gerronema nemorale: First report of the genus and species from Pakistan. Mycotaxon 136 (1): 249 - 259, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5248/136.249" title="Gerronema nemorale: First report of the genus and species from Pakistan." url="https://doi.org/10.5248/136.249" volume="136" year="2021">Aqdus and Khalid 2021</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="C3EBB1AC7568A6C6557B9842574F889D" class="Basidiomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="Gerronema" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Gerronema tenue" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="tenue">
<emphasis id="286D507AE2CC62B861964F880361B078" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Gerronema tenue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Dennis, described from Venezuela, is allied with 
<taxonomicName id="450282A2073D05571542AE4177A50870" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. nemorale" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis id="869F3DDC4E543991BD8545727A85A6DD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the latter differs in having a citrine yellow pileus, an insititious stipe, and lamellae edges without cheilocystidia (
<bibRefCitation id="1E9BCD5A4AF644FB10D08DF2E247AFBA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" author="Dennis, RWG" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="67 - 156" refId="B14" refString="Dennis, RWG, 1961. Fungi Venezuelani: IV Agaricales. Kew Bulletin 15 (1): 67 - 156, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" title="Fungi Venezuelani: IV Agaricales." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4115784" volume="15" year="1961">Dennis 1961</bibRefCitation>
). Another similar species, 
<taxonomicName id="45377AF1FE4D6ABCE60BB0286C85A746" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. corticiphilum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="corticiphilum">
<emphasis id="9463BE417503D4B3E8C0E22C9281DB6F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. corticiphilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Lj.N. Vassiljeva, described as 
<taxonomicName id="E3A12B2FAF944195C8AD1B563BBC7D13" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. corticiphila" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="corticiphila">
<emphasis id="427BE098C43E03C9A25E6FFE39E8C4B7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. corticiphila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has a rarely sulfurous-colored pileus and larger and narrower basidiospores (13-17 
<normalizedToken id="1E465739F5C977B857C1AB6AB03103F5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 
<normalizedToken id="73FABE7831467B49F9AC854496AD89C1" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="3E209B94363E963E2C14C931BFAFD693" author="Vassiljeva, LN" journalOrPublisher="Leningrad, Nauca" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" refId="B64" refString="Vassiljeva, LN, 1973. Die Blaetterpilze und Roehrlinge (Agaricales) von Primorsky Region. Leningrad, Nauca" title="Die Blaetterpilze und Roehrlinge (Agaricales) von Primorsky Region." year="1973">Vassiljeva 1973</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="A6F3568BE90A7C7EDC3BDE5E78E1CE2B" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. icterinum" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="icterinum">
<emphasis id="7F53E032AFDE254012926198422E699F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. icterinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Singer) Singer from South America, now treated as 
<taxonomicName id="1C83C4C3F3ECC401FF9D33CD0220EE97" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Trogia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Trogia icterina" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="icterina">
<emphasis id="831C31CFB135E91B1652AF6EDC2ADA76" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Trogia icterina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Singer) Corner, shows some similarities with 
<taxonomicName id="019C79BCED2980DFB73EFC22133AF899" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. nemorale" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis id="33A8C303FAE0036F2896B2895986BB2F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but has veined and forked lamellae and lacks cheilocystidia (
<bibRefCitation id="0477D8FBB4A4E4881227577B7AFDE423" author="Singer, R" journalOrPublisher="Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" refId="B58" refString="Singer, R, 1986. The Agaricales in modern taxonomy, 4th edn. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" title="The Agaricales in modern taxonomy, 4 th edn." year="1986">Singer 1986</bibRefCitation>
). Another species of 
<taxonomicName id="D7D432F43DAC6A1033AB00AA9BBCC6E4" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Marasmiaceae" genus="Trogia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Trogia" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BCC4EEC35C247B679FAF3E9C8659754E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Trogia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4CE86B67D8785757A622CA3607729A05" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Porotheleaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="T. mellea" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="mellea">
<emphasis id="4DC83F23FB04E2D3F300A45B48946E26" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">T. mellea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Corner, is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0C910DCA0D78DE378CBD388E8DE59E3A" genus="G." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="G. nemorale" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" rank="species" species="nemorale">
<emphasis id="E393F82B3C823BF616643071C0FC6B44" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">G. nemorale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be easily distinguished from the latter in having no olivaceous tones on the pileus surface, a fuscous, pruinose pileus center and stipe, and subclavate or subventricose cheilocystidia (
<bibRefCitation id="0D763C145FE5AAE937EDB8E2E1F28479" author="Corner, EJH" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, Oxford" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" refId="B11" refString="Corner, EJH, 1966. A monograph of cantharelloid fungi. Oxford University Press, Oxford" title="A monograph of cantharelloid fungi." year="1966">Corner 1966</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
